It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the use of deep learning techniques for graph-structured data is a popular research area in AI. 

The paper's focus on ConvNets suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), as ConvNets are commonly used in image processing tasks. 

The use of RNNs and LSTM suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which covers research on neural networks and their applications. 

Finally, the paper's focus on graph-structured data and its applications in various domains suggests it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which covers research on network analysis and its applications.
